  <h2 class="title">HISTORY OF PARLIAMENT ONLINE</h2> <h3>Terms and conditions of use</h3> <h3 style="text-align: justify;">Introduction</h3> <p style="text-align: justify;">By using this website, you signify that you have read and accept these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these Terms of Use, do not use the website. We reserve the right, at our discretion, to change, modify, add to or remove any of these terms at any time. Please check these terms periodically for changes. Your continued use of this website following the posting of changes to these terms will mean you accept those changes.</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><i>For our Privacy Policy and information on cookies, <a href="http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/help/privacy-and-cookies">please click here</a>.</i></p> <h3 style="text-align: justify;">Copyright</h3> <p style="text-align: justify;">Materials on this web site may be retrieved and downloaded solely for personal, educational and non-commercial use.</p> <p style="text-align: justify;">Copyright in each illustration that appears in the History of Parliament online is owned by the rights holder(s) named in 'Picture Details' window for that illustration. All rights are reserved. No illustration from the web site may be copied, modified, published or broadcast or otherwise distributed. <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br /> </span><br /> All other materials on this web site, including the organisation and layout of the site, are the copyright of the History of Parliament Trust or are reproduced with permission from other copyright owners. All rights are reserved.</p> <p style="text-align: justify;">No materials may otherwise be copied, modified, published, broadcast or otherwise distributed without the prior written permission of the History of Parliament Trust.</p> <p style="text-align: justify;">Reference may be made in any publication to the material on the website which is the copyright of the History of Parliament Trust on the understanding that any reference made to it in any publication will be properly acknowledged. No permission is granted thereby to reproduce the whole or a substantial part of the material or to make it available to the public in printed or electronic form (for example, on a website or disc).&nbsp; Any request for permission to reproduce the material or to publish substantial extracts should be addressed to the Director, The History of Parliament, 18   Bloomsbury Square, London WC1A 2NS.</p><h3 style="text-align: justify;">Liability</h3> <p style="text-align: justify;">Whilst the History of Parliament Trust shall use their reasonable endeavours to ensure that the information on this site is correct, the History of Parliament Trust shall not be liable for any loss or damage (including, without limitation, damages for loss of business or loss of profits) arising in contract, tort or otherwise from the use of this site or from the inability to use this site, or from the use of any information contained in it, or from any action or decision taken as a result of using this site or any such information.</p> <p style="text-align: justify;">The History of Parliament Trust reserves the right to change, modify, add to, or remove any of the content of this site at any time without prior notice. Articles in the 1832-68 section of the Website are in <b>draft form </b>and will be revised in due course.</p><h3 style="text-align: justify;">Disclaimer</h3> <p style="text-align: justify;">The History of Parliament Trust makes no warranties or representations of any kind concerning the accuracy or suitability of the information contained on this web site for any purpose. All such information is provided "as is" and with specific disclaimer of any warranties of merchantability, fitness for purpose, title and/or non-infringement. The History of Parliament Trust makes no warranties or representations of any kind that the services provided by this web site will be uninterrupted, error