story of Parliament Trust reserves the right to charge for access to the website, or any part of it, or for services associated with it, at some future date.</p><h3>User contributions</h3><p style="text-align: justify;">User contributions to our site are governed by <a href="http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/from-the-grassroots/community/user-guide">the community rules available here</a>.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">Content submitted to us will be owned by the individual contributor but the History of Parliament Trust will retain a non-exclusive perpetual royalty-free worldwide license to reproduce that content in any format. The History of Parliament Trust does not accept liability in respect of any material submitted by users and published by us and nor are we responsible for its content and accuracy. Contributors agree to indemnify HoP in full and permanently against any liabilities or costs we incur as a result of publishing material submitted by them.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">History of Parliament Trust reserves the right to publish, delete, edit or otherwise modify submitted material, and to include it in any media now known or later developed. Publication of any material remains at our sole discretion.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">Submission warrants that any submissions are the original work of the person making the submission, to which they own copyright and any other relevant rights. Material considered potentially libellous or defamatory, or potentially in breach of copyright, will be deleted.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">Any material considered to be commercial or spam will be deleted.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">Contributors who violate these terms and conditions may be suspended or banned from posting.<br /><br /></p> <h3 style="text-align: justify;">General</h3> <p style="text-align: justify;">By accessing any part of this site, you shall be deemed to have accepted these terms in full.</p><p style="text-align